did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY
did.unittitle: Alain Giami collection on sexual practices and attitudes and their health outcomes, circa 1980-2016.
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: The collection contains faculty research papers as well as documentation (i.e., erotic and pornographic magazines) from sub-Saharan Africa, Brazil, France, Norway, and the United States.
did.langmaterial: Collection material in French, Norwegian, Portuguese, and English

bioghist.head: BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE
bioghist.p: French socal scientist, director of research at the Institut national de la santé et de la recherche médicale. He works particularly on the use of the condom, the sexuality of disabled people, and the attitudes of medical doctors and nurses.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: The collection contains faculty research papers as well as documentation (i.e., erotic and pornographic magazines) from sub-Saharan Africa, Brazil, France, Norway, and the United States.
